Interface DependencyFilter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultDependencyFilter

    public interface DependencyFilter
    Dependency Filter contract for Customization to filter dependents based on a given set of XMLFilter entries

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        java.util.Collection<XMLFilterEntry> execute(java.util.Collection<XMLFilterEntry> inputEntries,
                                             TransformationContext context)
                                      throws TransformationException
        Execute the dependency filter for a given set of input XMLFilterEntries. This method will be executed in recursion for incremental set of filters which are created due to exclusion few more set of objects
        Parameters:
        inputEntries - Input entries can be either initial set of XMLFilterEntries which are created based on xpath and property based filtering. OR it can be an incremental set of XMLFilterEntries which are passed during recursion.
        context -
        Returns:
        Incremental set of XMLFilterEntries which are used for execution of next set of dependents

        Supported API: true
        Throws:
        TransformationException
